  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Brazilian Agriculture: Coordinating Organizations, Communities and Families to Regionalize Agroecological Innovations at the Southern End of Bahia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is designed to strengthen the grassroots movement in southern Bahia by confronting social and environmental degradation from the advancing eucalyptus monoculture in the region. Action will be taken to promote agroecological innovations for the 400 families and 20 communities involved in the project. Political, technical, and administrative capacity building will also be promoted using a supportive exchange of resources, which will result in greater food security for families. The proposal will be implemented by the non-governmental organization Tierra Viva, under the auspices of the Network for Agroecology and Family Farming at the Southern End of Bahia.</narrative>
  </description>
